Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Half the @new potatoes{1}(halved) and put on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle on a little @olive oil{} and half the @dried thyme{1/4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat and spread out evenly. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30%minutes}. Place your hand flat on top of one of the @British chicken breasts{2} and slice it from the side so it opens like a book. Repeat for all breasts (remember to wash your hands afterwards!).

Remove the top and bottom from the @carrot{2} and @courgette{1}. Chop both into batons the size of your index finger. Pop on another lined baking tray, drizzle over some @olive oil{} and season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and the remaining @dried thyme{1/4%tsp}. Toss to coat, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft, ~{20%minutes}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1/2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Put a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the chicken with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Brown for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side then remove from the pan. When the potatoes have had 15 mins cooking time, shake the tray to turn them and pop the chicken on top. Roast together for the remaining ~{15%minutes} cooking time.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== Crème Fraîche Mixture ==

Put the @crème fraiche{1} in a #small bowl{} and mix in the garlic and half the parsley.

> Use less garlic if you're not a fan.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{15%g} in another #bowl{} with the remaining parsley, the @olive oil{1} and a pinch of @salt{}.

== Assembly ==

When the potatoes, chicken and veggies are ready, remove from the oven and switch your grill to medium-high. Put the carrots and courgettes together with the potatoes and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Transfer the chicken to the empty tray and cool for ~{3%minutes}. Spoon the crème fraîche mixture on each chicken breast then cover with the breadcrumbs. Grill until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Be careful - the crumbs burn easily!

Share the veggies between your plates and sit a garlicky chicken breast alongside. Serve any remaining crème fraîche as a dipping sauce. Enjoy!